e. Die Studie untersucht die Dispenspraxis in den vier Diözesen Brixen, Chur, Salzburg und Trient. Sie verknüpft die aufwändigen kirchlichen und staatlichen Verfahrenswege mit Logiken der häuslichen Organisation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access. Unless otherwise specified individually in the content, the work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives (CC BY-NC-ND) license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.vr-elibrary.de/page/open-access  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jun 2020) 0aConsanguinity (Canon law) 0aConsanguinity (Canon law). 0aConsanguinity (Law) 0aConsanguinity (Law)zAustria. 0aConsanguinityzAustria. 0aCross-cousin marriagezAustria. 0aDispensations (Law)zEuropexHistory. 0aDispensationsxHistory. 0aMarriage lawzEuropexHistory. 0aMarriagezEuropexHistory. 4aEhe, Eheverbote, Verwandtschaft. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7767/9783205794110zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783205794110.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA